{meta: title Calling My Children Home}
{meta: artist Emmylou Harris}
{meta: writer Doyle Lawson, Charles Waller, Robert Yates}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Those lives were mine to love and cherish
[G7]To guard and guide along life's way
[C]Oh God forbid that one should perish
[G7]That one alas should go [C]astray
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Back in the years with all together
[G7]Around the place we'd romp and play
[C]So lonely now I oft' times wonder
[G7]Oh will they come back home some [C]day
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]I'm lonesome for my precious [C]children
[G7]They live so far away
[C]Oh may they hear my [F]calling  [C]calling
[G7]And come back home some [C]day
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
I gave my all for my dear children
[G7]Their problems still with love I share
[C]I'd brave life's storm defy the tempest
[G7]To bring them home from [C]anywhere
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
I lived my life my love I gave them
[G7]To guide them through this world of strife
[C]I hope and pray we'll live together
[G7]In that great glad here after [C]life
{end_of_verse}

